00:16:47,207 --> 00:16:48,121
Later!

257
00:16:49,009 --> 00:16:51,359
JoJo, be careful!

258
00:16:51,656 --> 00:16:54,444
Make sure you come back in one piece, okay?!

259
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:55,643
Don't get pushy.

260
00:16:55,785 --> 00:16:59,593
You may be an old lady before
I get back, but I will return.

261
00:17:01,576 --> 00:17:02,636
Oh, yeah?

262
00:17:03,018 --> 00:17:05,264
You stupid jerk!

263
00:17:14,911 --> 00:17:17,230
I'll be back a lot sooner than you think.

264
00:18:06,269 --> 00:18:08,491
Hey, drive the damned car, will you?

265
00:18:08,516 --> 00:18:10,630
Huh? What happened to your arms, man?

266
00:18:10,701 --> 00:18:12,368
Huh? Aah!

267
00:18:12,420 --> 00:18:15,792
Something's wrong with the
wheel, man! I can't get it to move!

268
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:20,878
Hmm.

269
00:18:21,061 --> 00:18:23,396
Esidisi hasn't reported back.

270
00:18:23,765 --> 00:18:27,408
He last said that he had learned
the stone was somewhere in venice.

271
00:18:27,796 --> 00:18:30,348
I wonder if something has happened to him.

272
00:18:33,131 --> 00:18:34,033
Hey, JoJo.

273
00:18:34,323 --> 00:18:35,065
JoJo.

274
00:18:36,951 --> 00:18:38,578
JoJo, wake up.

275
00:18:39,450 --> 00:18:40,572
Huh? Wha...

276
00:18:40,818 --> 00:18:42,949
JoJo, we've caught up with the train.

277
00:18:43,483 --> 00:18:46,038
They're going through their customs check at the moment.

278
00:18:46,277 --> 00:18:47,603
That works in our favor.

279
00:18:47,691 --> 00:18:49,877
We're less than an hour from St. Moritz,

280
00:18:49,902 --> 00:18:52,061
which leaves us enough time to get ready.

281
00:18:52,371 --> 00:18:53,855
It's good we caught up.

282
00:18:54,231 --> 00:18:56,119
Come on, JoJo. Look sharp.

283
00:18:57,143 --> 00:19:02,310
Listen, I'm just saving up my strength for
the big battle, that's all. Get off my case.

284
00:19:02,754 --> 00:19:05,972
Let's hurry up and get there
so we can retrieve that stone.

285
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:09,277
Then we're gonna need some sort
of plan for the fight with Wamuu.

286
00:19:09,634 --> 00:19:11,724
We'll wait for that until we cross.

287
00:19:14,845 --> 00:19:16,205
What the hell?

288
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,326
Knock it off!

289
00:19:18,393 --> 00:19:21,275
If you want to go on, just quit honking, and pass us.

290
00:19:22,156 --> 00:19:23,735
German soldiers.

291
00:19:24,223 --> 00:19:28,266
What the hell are they doing in a
car on the swiss‐italian border?

292
00:19:30,866 --> 00:19:33,414
Well, well, you're looking rather spry.

293
00:19:33,482 --> 00:19:36,569
My, you have grown so much, Joestar.

294
00:19:36,901 --> 00:19:39,324
Huh? W‐what did you say, mister?

295
00:19:41,670 --> 00:19:42,900
What was that about?

296
00:19:43,407 --> 00:19:44,829
G‐get back here!

297
00:19:45,232 --> 00:19:49,646
Who the hell are you?! What's going
on? I don't know any German soldiers.

298
00:19:49,714 --> 00:19:51,322
Hey, look at the train.

299
00:19:51,716 --> 00:19:53,451
So many soldiers.

300
00:19:54,197 --> 00:19:56,122
Hey, major, we found the package!

301
00:19:56,678 --> 00:19:59,444
The crest. Look. They've got the package.

302
00:19:59,469 --> 00:20:01,635
Yeah, and we all know what's inside.

303
00:20:07,903 --> 00:20:09,428
The Red Stone of Aja!

304
00:20:09,892 --> 00:20:12,562
I don't understand. Why do the Germans want it?

305
00:20:12,663 --> 00:20:17,953
We have decided to take the stone as a
specimen for our scientific research program.

306
00:20:18,448 --> 00:20:19,907
For the past three weeks,

307
00:20:19,971 --> 00:20:24,207
we have been watching your every
move while you were operating in venice.

308
00:20:24,445 --> 00:20:28,250
We began the surveillance when we lost our team in Rome.

309
00:20:28,503 --> 00:20:31,483
We saw your training, we saw Esidisi,

310
00:20:31,658 --> 00:20:33,906
and we knew you were chasing the stone.

311
00:20:35,123 --> 00:20:38,809
Now, our base is set up at a lodge up ahead.

312
00:20:38,974 --> 00:20:40,015
Follow us.

313
00:20:40,779 --> 00:20:44,767
We want to ask a few questions
about the stone und about Kars.

314
00:20:45,138 --> 00:20:47,143
Why not work together, eh?

315
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,845
After all, we are not complete strangers, JoJo.

316
00:20:51,087 --> 00:20:53,540
Hey! What are you blabbering about?

317
00:20:53,929 --> 00:20:56,471
Don't think you know anything about me, you bastard!

318
00:20:56,749 --> 00:20:59,219
If the Germans are here, that means...

319
00:20:59,338 --> 00:21:00,687
What do we do, coach?

320
00:21:01,546 --> 00:21:02,818
We have to follow them.

321
00:21:03,492 --> 00:21:06,401
At least we know Kars doesn't have the red stone either.

322
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:11,987
At that time, the German army was marching
across Europe, taking country after country.

323
00:21:12,138 --> 00:21:16,373
They wanted to ensure their rule across
the continent would last indefinitely.

324
00:21:16,932 --> 00:21:20,932
The power of the mask and red stone
would solve their problem perfectly

325
00:21:21,086 --> 00:21:23,841
by giving them everything they would need to prevail.

326
00:21:24,041 --> 00:21:27,741
The Germans were planning to use
the ultimate power of immortality

327
00:21:27,921 --> 00:21:29,741
to conquer the world.

